item.title: Report E-2024090324
item.description:
Report E-2024090324

Identified by scraper @ 2024-09-18T09:15:04+00:00

  • Incident Date: 2024-08-21
  • City: GREENCASTLE
  • State: PA
  • Report Type: A hazardous material incident
  • Mode Of Transportation: Highway
  • Carrier/Reporter: XPO LOGISTICS, LLC
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Total Amount Of Damages: 0
  • Serious Incident Ind: No
  • Description: XPO terminal XHG notified ERTS of a cargo release. It was reported that approximately 10-Gallons of RPM Finish Works 984-7007 released from a 55-gallon drum due to forklift puncture. The release impacted dock floor. No storm drains or waterways are reported to be impacted by the release. ERTS reviewed the SDS with XPO who confirmed terminal personnel are comfortable and capable of cleaning the release donning the proper PPE per the SDS. The terminal used a 65-gallon drum for waste, which was staged on site for personnel to manage.
